The paper presents a machine learning system that can automatically generate software programs, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The system uses genetic algorithms (GA) and programming language-specific genome construction and elimination techniques, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL) research. The paper also discusses the system's design and performance, which could be relevant to software development (cs.SD) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
